commit.title: [omega] Error on non-documented and deprecated "omega with *"
commit.message:
[omega] Error on non-documented and deprecated "omega with *"

This prepares for its removal in 8.12, IMHO it is important as to
allow us to get rid of omega for 8.12 too.

I made the warning fatal for now as to identify who's using it; we
should make it non-fatal in 8.11.

Question, should we add the same message to bare `omega` ?

Maybe 8.11 is a good moment to suggest users to exchange `omega` for
`lia` ?

This prepares for its removal in 8.12, IMHO it is important as to
allow us to get rid of omega for 8.12 too.

I made the warning fatal for now as to identify who's using it; we
should make it non-fatal in 8.11.

Question, should we add the same message to bare `omega` ?

Maybe 8.11 is a good moment to suggest users to exchange `omega` for
`lia` ?
